rComments: very knowledgeable, but very difficult to understand. content is already quite hard to grasp, so this makes things much more difficult. midterm was hard (typical for higher level eco courses). is available for office hours and replies fast. uottawa needs to do a rehaul of their economic theory professors

People saying students are not working hard for their school during the online class. now move your attention to this professor as well. She only teaches once a week and left a very messy material online to let you figure it out and don't even care if you understand or not. The way she replies to my email is very arrogant and rude.
She is honestly so rude and talks to students like they are a piece of garbage just because she knows that students cannot swear back at her face since she is in a position of power.

Professor Lilia is very helpful and very clear about her expectations, even though she provides no solutions to problems but she is accessible during office hours and always answers her emails. The Group projects are demanding but also interesting and allows you to apply what you studied to real world!

Great prof. Really enjoys teaching the content, and really knows her stuff. Course based on 3 projects that actually concern interesting things and useful software/applications. Easy midterm. Intriguing readings. Caring prof, easy grader. Show up and get an A - but if you want to learn a lot you can learn too. Participation matters. Would recommend

Super nice prof, actually cares about students. Very clear expectations, always willing to help outside of class. Lecture slides cover everything you need to know, and if you go to class you'll know exactly what to know for the midterm. Puts *Everything* online. Easy tests, Solid choice overall. I do find her lectures a bit boring though.
Hard to understand. Tough exam. Tough grader. She was the absolute worst

She is a great professor. Her lectures are heavily based off a power point that she makes available online, so you can just sit and listen, however most mathematical explanations are done on the bored (which is nice because it is easy to follow). She gives you online assignments with unlimited tries. In class participation marks. Easy-fair midterm.
Not very helping when ask questions

Poor professor, does not care about her students. She mumbles a lot so its hard to understand her and plus she has thick accent. Her midterms and finals are extremely hard and are all over the place. Avoid taking her if you can. I would have dropped her class if the course wasn't mandatory.

Overall the course is easy, 20% of your grade are online quizzes with unlimited attempts (pretty much 100% for 20%). Midterm was easy, Final wasn't cumulative, also easy. Many concepts are repeated from intro to macro. Lectures are extremely dry, you're better off reading the textbook and slides.

Not bad but not great either... a lot of material to cover as she assigns textbook chapters to read each week along with supplementary articles, practice questions and homework, on top of the lecture slides.. the material itself can be challenging. Practice the online questions as the exams consist of similar (if not identical) questions

This is like the most frustrating course I have ever taken , the test and final were all over the place after telling us to study some specific part before the exam , if this wasnt a compulsory course I would have dropped it. Horrible horrible horrible avoid at all cost

Good professor! Cares about students and answers emails quickly. The course itself consists of a midterm, final, and 8 easy online assignments with unlimited attempts. The exam questions are very similar to the online homework questions. Her lecture slides are excellent! I barely needed the textbook aside from the online access code.

I would recommend to try your best to avoid her. She is like an agent from publishing company. She leads you to buy the textbook and oline access quiz by explaining questions like see page  of the text book. Her lectures are extremely dry, and what I felt was that she does lectures for her own satisfaction, not really think on the students side
dry, no command of the class.
Terrible prof! Difficult assignments and exams, and even worse lectures that don't prepare you for them.

A good prof. You get used to her accent pretty quickly and she is easy to understand. Her lectures are boring but all her slides get posted and you don't need to go to class to do well (although it is often helpful). All the assignments can be done easily after reading the textbook and exams are fair with no surprises.

She is one of the worst teachers I have had in my undergrad. Her accent is not THAT bad, but what bugs me is that she can't lecture without pausing for "umms" and "uhhs" which really distracts my learning. You're better off staying at home and reading the textbook/slides. She never connected with the class. She seems uncomfortable teaching.
She is extremely hard to understand. Maybe she knows her stuff but it's how to communicate it clearly that matters as a teacher.

Despite finishing with an A+, I must say this was one of the worst professors I have ever had. She is very unclear and seems confused throughout her lectures. Thankfully she uses everything from the textbook so just study that. Avoid if you can.

I don't think she is as bad as people make her seem. She does have a very thick accent and can be hard to understand, but she writes a lot on the board and it's mostly math so it's not that hard to follow. Her exams are tough but you will learn a lot. She's not a bad marker either, the average for the midterm in my class was 75 %.
Not a bad prof, but boring class since it is hard to understand her

She is honestly a terrible teacher despite that she seems like a really smart women. Watch out for her grading she does not grade fairly marks depend on whether she likes you or not despite your answers
Awesome prof, very helpful.

Lectures slides were detailed and organized; writes a lot of notes on the board as well. Exams were not overly difficult, hard marker though. Assignments are graded for completion and worth 5% of grade.
Great course! Great Professor!
one of the worst prof. that I even had. Her assignments almost had nothing to do with the context in class. She never made the questions easily to understand. Do not take here class

I found that I had to learn about the subject entirely on my own from the text. She did not teach well(read off slides in monotone.)Maybe she knows her stuff, but as a teacher, she is ineffective.

Avoid her like the Plague. No confidence, Lectures = reading off slides.  I went to see her about my exam, I spoke to 5 other profs who agreed that I was correct, she then asked to remark my whole exam and tried finding mistakes where there were none.  She's still a young professor, she needs to accept criticism. Hopefully she will improve!

One of the poorest professors I've ever had. She is not confident when she teaches and also can't seem to answer students questions. Her exams are pretty easy though as questions are all from the text/SG.
In class, she's pretty clear. Sometimes gets confused when ask questions, but easy to follow, especially with textbook.
Brilliant course, clearly knows her macro economics, exam and mid terms are based on problems from the book - very fair.

I think she is pretty good as a teacher.  I went to get help from her and it worked out great.  I notice her exam used many questions from the assignments. It was tough but I learned alot.
